(ABSTRACT) Tj
0 -13 Td
() Tj
0 -13 Td
() Tj
0 -13 Td
(This paper evaluates whether India should adopt an export-led growth \(ELG\) strategy in the 21st century,) Tj
0 -13 Td
(given global trade deceleration, geopolitical fragmentation, and supply-chain realignment. The central) Tj
0 -13 Td
(question is not whether exports matter for growth—an established proposition—but whether a *pure ELG) Tj
0 -13 Td
(model* remains feasible for a large, late-industrializing democracy with India’s factor endowments,) Tj
0 -13 Td
(institutional constraints, and domestic market size. I develop a unified framework spanning comparative) Tj
0 -13 Td
(advantage, Heckscher-Ohlin, new trade theory, and endogenous growth mechanisms to identify channels) Tj
0 -13 Td
(through which exports can raise long-run growth: productivity, scale economies, learning-by-exporting,) Tj
0 -13 Td
(technology diffusion, capital deepening, and labor reallocation.) Tj
0 -13 Td
() Tj
0 -13 Td
(Empirically, the paper proposes and implements a reproducible strategy for India \(2000–2024\) combining) Tj
0 -13 Td
(national time-series and state-level panel models, including fixed effects and instrumental variables.) Tj
0 -13 Td
(Baseline estimates indicate that export growth is positively associated with GDP growth and) Tj
0 -13 Td
(manufacturing employment, but magnitudes vary by sectoral composition and external demand cycles. IV) Tj
0 -13 Td
(estimates using partner-country import-demand shocks suggest that endogeneity biases OLS downward in) Tj
0 -13 Td
(some specifications and upward in others, implying omitted-policy and reverse-causality channels. Event-) Tj
0 -13 Td
(study evidence around major trade-policy and global-shock episodes shows asymmetry: export booms) Tj
0 -13 Td
(generate broad productivity spillovers, while export collapses are partially cushioned by domestic) Tj
0 -13 Td
(demand and services resilience.) Tj
0 -13 Td
() Tj
